@startuml Data Flow Diagram
!theme plain

title Data Flow Diagram - Solar Energy Calculator

actor User

rectangle "User Interface Layer" {
    rectangle "Home Page" as HomePage
    rectangle "Google Map Component" as MapComp
    rectangle "System Specs Form" as SpecsForm
    rectangle "Solar Results Component" as ResultsComp
}

rectangle "API Layer" {
    rectangle "/api/solar" as SolarAPI
    rectangle "/api/calculate" as CalcAPI
}

rectangle "External Services" {
    database "PVGIS API" as PVGIS
    database "Google Maps API" as GMaps
}

User --> HomePage : 1. Loads application

HomePage --> MapComp : 2. Renders map interface

MapComp --> GMaps : 3. Fetches map tiles\nand location data

GMaps --> MapComp : 4. Returns map imagery

User --> MapComp : 5. Selects location\n(click/search/drag)

MapComp --> GMaps : 6. Reverse geocode\ncoordinates

GMaps --> MapComp : 7. Returns address

MapComp --> HomePage : 8. Sends Location\n{lat, lng, address}

User --> SpecsForm : 9. Enters system specs\n(area, efficiency, etc.)

SpecsForm --> HomePage : 10. Sends SystemSpecs\n{area, panelEfficiency, ...}

User --> HomePage : 11. Clicks "Calculate"

HomePage --> SolarAPI : 12. GET /api/solar\n?lat={lat}&lng={lng}

SolarAPI --> PVGIS : 13. Requests irradiance data\nwith parameters

PVGIS --> SolarAPI : 14. Returns SolarData\n{yearlyIrradiance, monthlyData,\noptimalTilt, optimalAzimuth}

SolarAPI --> HomePage : 15. Returns formatted\nSolarData (JSON)

HomePage --> CalcAPI : 16. POST /api/calculate\n{solarData, systemSpecs}

CalcAPI --> CalcAPI : 17. Calculates:\n- Energy production\n- Number of panels\n- CO₂ savings\n- Financial metrics

CalcAPI --> HomePage : 18. Returns SolarEstimate\n{yearlyEnergyKwh, numberOfPanels,\nco2SavingsKg, financialSavings, ...}

HomePage --> ResultsComp : 19. Passes estimate\nand solarData

ResultsComp --> User : 20. Displays results,\ncharts, and metrics

note right of SolarAPI
  Error Handling:
  - Validates coordinates
  - 10s timeout on PVGIS
  - Fallback estimation
  - Returns consistent format
end note

note right of CalcAPI
  Calculations:
  - Energy = Area × Irradiance × 
    Efficiency × SystemEfficiency
  - Panels = floor(Area / PanelArea)
  - CO₂ = Energy × Regional Factor
  - Savings = Energy × Electricity Rate
end note

note left of MapComp
  User Interactions:
  - Address search (autocomplete)
  - Click on map to place marker
  - Drag marker to new position
  - All update location state
end note

@enduml
